cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on the performance evaluation of a MAC protocol for power-line communications, which is a type of network. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely, as the paper deals with the transmission of data over a noisy channel and proposes a performance model for the protocol. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category, as the paper studies the dynamics of the protocol and how it is affected by the deferral counter. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely, but still possible, as power-line communications can be used for multimedia applications such as video streaming. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also a possible category, as the paper focuses on evaluating the performance of the MAC protocol and proposes a new model to improve accuracy.
